The fired employee took revenge, bought laptops for the company and sold them
After being dismissed, the disgraced employee bought computers for the company and then sold them.
He managed to spend the money before being detained by the police.
Within a short time, the man bought a total of sixteen computers for more than two hundred thousand crowns in twelve cases.
"After taking over the notebooks, he took them to Olomouc, where he sold them in bazaars," said Chief Commissioner of the Šumperk Police Rostislav Brückner.
The motive for the fraud was revenge on the employer for dismissal and also to gain money.
"During the interrogation, he told us that he used the money to repay loans," Brückner said.
Police also found that the impostor was a pathological gambler who had been repeatedly treated in a psychiatric ward.
The money could also end up in slot machines or video lottery terminals.
"The fact is that we did not find any money from him," the commissioner said.
A fraudster who has already been convicted of theft once now faces between one and five years in prison.
Police have not yet said whether bazaars that bought the laptops below cost and resold them are also facing punishment.
"It is true that they were taking over brand new goods, which is suspicious to say the least," the commissioner said.
However, none of the owners of the bazaar has yet been charged.
