In addition to Chegg and Amazon, eBay Inc's Half.com are also popular alternatives to buying used books.
Lending
It is also worth considering borrowing textbooks if you treat them well, do not forget to return them and do not need to have them after the seminar.
You can save up to 80% of the cost of a new book.
For example, a student could borrow a "Calculus" for about twenty dollars for the entire semester.
Familiarize yourself with the terms and conditions of the store where you rent the book, including penalties for notes, highlighting, or wear and tear, and damage.
Keep in mind: If you do not return the book in time, the fine may be higher than the price of the new book.
E-books
